I still lurk on boards some even though I don't play anymore, and have been watching the whole thing on ST and here.<br>
<br>
Simply put, the issue of whether Hayley's sig is okay is between her, and the artists involved. The rest of you are just using this as a basis for personal attacks.<br>
<br>
If you want to get something off of your chest in regards to Hayley's conduct that actually has something to do with you, hey, great. But have the guts to actually come out and talk about YOUR issues, not try and act as if you're championing someone else's cause, because frankly, I don't believe any of you care one whit about protecting the work of the artists involved.<br>
<br>
That being said, Hayley, you really need to (and may already be) work with the artists whose work is involved and try to come up with something that everyone can agree on. If that means scrapping the new sig entirely, then you need to do that; you have to respect the artists' wishes in how their work is used. Not because of copyright law or anything like that, but because it's the right thing to do.<br>
<br>
The rest of you, hop off the bandwagon.  <br>
